 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search ENGINEER - RESEARCH ENGINEER - SIGNAL TECHNOLOGIES Southwest Research Institute 137 reviews San Antonio, TX 78238 Southwest Research Institute 137 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. The Signal Technologies Section within the Tactical Products department focuses on signal processing capabilities for mobile platforms in challenging environments. 
 Objectives of this Role:
 Design, develop, integrate, test, document, and deploy signal processing capabilities for applications in specialized radio communication, radiolocation, and electronic warfare programs 
Create and refine innovative solutions and algorithms for automatic detection, recognition, demodulation, decoding, and geolocation of communication and electronic signals, to include the application of machine learning techniques 
Assist with research objectives and efforts focused on developing new signal processing capabilities that can be deployed to meet customer needs 
 Daily and Monthly Responsibilities:
 Support multi-disciplinary software, hardware and firmware development teams. Interact directly with project team, project management, and technical customer to fully understand the task objectives and opportunities 
Opportunities for short-term travel to government facilities/military bases or other customer facilities for system installations and to provide technical support 
 Requirements:
 Requires a Bachelors or a Masters with a 3.00 GPA in Electrical Engineering or Computer Engineering 
1-5 years: If without a Masters degree, post graduate work experience in digital signal processing and wireless communications in addition to relevant coursework 
Must have coursework or internship in digital signal processing, wireless communications, or machine learning. 
0-5 years: Masters degree with coursework or internship focus on digital signal processing, wireless communications, image processing, or signals & systems 
0-5 years: Masters degree with coursework or internship focus on machine learning, deep learning, or artificial intelligence 
Requires coursework and interest in software applications for software defined radio, digital signal processing, wireless communications, signal modulation, or machine learning. 
Must be familiar with Matlab, Python, C/C++, and Linux 
Experience with or an interest in software defined radio (SDR) and related frameworks such as GNU radio . 
Experience in or an interest in Verilog, VHDL, or OpenCL, as well as hardware and software testing for both embedded hardware (FPGAs) and software (C/C++) 
Requires excellent interpersonal skills and must be able to work on a team 
A valid/clear driver's license is required 
 Special Requirements:
 Applicant selected will be subject to a government security investigation and must meet eligibility requirements for access to classified information. Applicant must be a U.S. citizen. Southwest Research Institute 7 days ago original job Report job Apply Now Apply On Company Site Save this job Save this job Research Engineer jobs in San Antonio, TX Jobs at Southwest Research Institute in San Antonio, TX Research Engineer salaries in San Antonio, TX Company Info Follow Get job updates from Southwest Research Institute Southwest Research Institute 137 reviews Southwest Research Institute (SwRI), headquartered in San Antonio, Texas, is one of the oldest and largest independent, nonprofit, applie... Let employers find you Thousands of employers search for candidates on Indeed Upload your resume Hiring Lab Career Advice Browse Jobs Browse Companies Salaries Find Certifications Indeed Events Work at Indeed Countries About Help Center Â© 2021 Indeed Do Not Sell My Personal Information Accessibility at Indeed Privacy Center Cookies Privacy Terms Let Employers Find You Upload Your Resume 
 
 
 
 
 
